<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>dockerdynomesh — {{.MachineName}}</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 720px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; }
    code, pre { background: #f4f4f4; padding: 0.2em 0.4em; border-radius: 3px; }
    pre { padding: 1em; overflow-x: auto; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>dockerdynomesh on {{.MachineName}}</h1>
  <p>This machine runs <a href="https://github.com/leonletto/dockerdynomesh">dockerdynomesh</a>. Containers here are reachable at:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>https://&lt;service&gt;.&lt;project&gt;.{{.Suffix}}/</code> &mdash; from this machine</li>
    {{- if .TailnetHost}}
    <li><code>https://&lt;service&gt;.&lt;project&gt;.{{.TailnetHost}}/</code> &mdash; from the tailnet</li>
    {{- end}}
  </ul>
  <h2>Trust this machine's CA</h2>
  <p>If your browser shows a cert warning, that's expected — you haven't trusted this CA yet. That's what the next step fixes.</p>
  <p>One-liner (verifies the cert against the live TLS endpoint before installing):</p>
  <pre>curl -sSL http://{{.SetupHost}}/install.sh | bash</pre>
  <p>Or do it manually:</p>
  <pre>
# 1. Download
curl -O http://{{.SetupHost}}/root.crt

# 2. Verify against the live TLS endpoint (any service hostname works;
#    we use a known-good name on this machine)
echo | openssl s_client -connect {{.TailnetHost}}:443 \
       -CAfile root.crt -verify_return_error 2&gt;&amp;1 | grep "Verify return code"

# 3. Install (macOS)
sudo security add-trusted-cert -d -r trustRoot \
     -k /Library/Keychains/System.keychain root.crt

# 3. Install (Ubuntu)
sudo cp root.crt /usr/local/share/ca-certificates/dockerdynomesh-{{.MachineName}}.crt
sudo update-ca-certificates
</pre>
</body>
</html>
